<title>USA: American Business sells Vanier for $47 mln.</title>
<headline>American Business sells Vanier for $47 mln.</headline>
<dateline>ATLANTA 1997-01-02</dateline>
<text>
<p>American Business Products Inc said on Thursday that it has sold its Vanier Graphics subsidiary to Reynolds and Reynolds Co for $47 million in cash and the assumption of certain current liabilities of the business.</p>
<p>The purchase price is subject to adjustment based upon Vanier's closing balance sheet.</p>
<p>American Business said that Vanier, a forms manufacturer and provider of forms management and work flow analysis, had 1995 sales of about $150 million.</p>
